ance of #104843 has shown that bugs might still be in hiding for let chains. In order to make the implementation of let chains in rustc more robust, it would be useful to increase the number of places let chains are tested in.\r\n\r\nThere is an automatted tool to convert uses of the `if_chain` crate to let chains: https://github.com/Alexendoo/if-to-let-chain\r\n\r\nOne ways to increase testing would be to run the tool on some of the users of `if_chain`, e.g. clippy. Maybe this brings up new bugs like #104843.\r\n\r\n@rustbot label F-let_chains", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/104893/reactions", "total_count": 2, "+1": 2, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/104893/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}